The Telegraph - Calcutta : International

 Clooney injured

 Los Angeles, Sept 22 (Reuters): Movie star George Clooney fractured a rib and his girlfriend broke her foot when the two were knocked off his motorcycle by a car in New Jersey yesterday.

 Clooney, 46, and his companion, Sarah Larson, were treated for their injuries at the Palisades Medical Center, across the Hudson river from Manhattan, and were released. He was treated for a hairline fracture of a rib and road rash, he said. Larson, who was a passenger on the motorcycle driven by Clooney, suffered a broken foot. Both were wearing helmets. 




